svg:text.svg:tspan: Ciaran Carson was born in Belfast in 1948. This poem was written in 1990 during the Troubles.
This was a 30-year conflict which saw lots of violence take place between Irish nationalists and unionists.
Effects of conflict, individual experiences, fear...

this poem with ‘Exposure’ — both present the horrors of conflict from a realistic, first-person perspective.
